{"questionId":"27961","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Six restaurant locations (labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>E</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext></math>) are shown, together with their Voronoi&nbsp;diagram. All distances are measured in kilometres.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/acc0315b5119f8e934ef7f20a3ae6df2c39a32af.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Elena wants to eat at the closest restaurant to her. Write down the restaurant she&nbsp;should go to, if she is at</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>,&nbsp;when restaurant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> is closed.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>F</mtext></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27961","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.3a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"0, 1, when restaurant A is closed.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}